text: hi everyone quick thingy quick tano here
the internet's busiest music nerd and
it's time for a review of the new
quickly quickly album the long and short
of it this is a music project
masterminded by singer
multi-instrumentalist producer and
songwriter mr graham johnson if you
scour the internet these days you can
find a fairly large amount of bedroom
brood pop and r b projects out there but
rarely do i come across one with a
neo-soul flare some textured sound play
and a taste for jazz melodicism too and
that's basically what mr johnson has
turned quickly quickly into on this
record past tracks have also indulged in
stuff like lo-fi hip-hop and glitch hop
which isn't surprising considering how
textured chunky and groovy a lot of the
beats in this tracklist are there are
kind of some general issues though that
i had with the album the flow of this
record for one is a little choppy and
the vocal performances while
they're definitely in line with that diy
aesthetic sometimes they do come off a
bit too average or even comatose with
cuts like come visit me as well as i am
close to the river suffering especially
in those passages where the vocals kind
of need to carry things in the midst of
all this like shimmering spacey
instrumentation that being said i did
walk away impressed by the vast majority
of what quickly quickly presented here
as the lyrics are consistently
thoughtful the melodies are pretty sharp
the production is so varied and creative
and while on the whole it's maybe a bit
too disjointed to be greater than the
sum of its parts many of these cuts on
an individual level are great like the
first track phases which kicks off with
this great spoken word intro from sharif
simmons i do love it but it kind of sets
the
stage for what i assumed was going to be
some kind of like
flying lotus futuristic psych jazz
experience the following tune though is
beautiful and kind of tense in its
melodic progressions it's got a great
groove that gets even better as johnson
lets loose with some beefier kicks and
bass laced with these raw guitar leads i
also love the subtly trippy sax passages
that follow through from there then she
is a groovy alternative r b cut with
loads of lush layers surreal effects
even forlorn vocal leads that i think
some joji fans could get into once the
song establishes itself it kind of moves
through a bunch of instrumental
variations topped with these angelic
falsetto vocal harmonies just a truly
lovely and euphoric vibe meanwhile the
nimble vocal melodies on the track feel
are captivating and shine a lot brighter
than the humble delivery would imply
johnson also flexes his talents as a
lyricist on this track talking about the
emotional strife in his life drawing
some parallels from that to a film and
then blurring the lines between the two
then the song everything is different to
me really stuck to me thanks to its
acoustic guitar passages it's
dejected and somewhat hypnotizing vocals
and grooves but everything's different
to me
this is easily one of the most strange
and unlikely ear worms on the entire
project but yeah despite being so
low-key this somehow stuck out to me as
being one of the most addictive songs on
the record and generally the more
acoustic and folk-inspired cuts go over
pretty well so while i walked away from
this thing impressed by a decent amount
of tracks some of the vocals really did
leave something to be desired and again
i think this record overall really
struggled to
come together with a cohesive sound
direction something there's a lot of
great ideas and raw talent on this
record and on these songs but i'm hoping
that at some point everything with
quickly quickly just solidifies into
something a bit more firm and i guess
material or maybe even pushes things
into even wilder and more unpredictable
territory with more genre fusions and
maybe even more guest artists but
ultimately i don't know what the future
holds all i can tell you is that i like
this record and i think it has a
load of potential if it continues
digging
in the vicinity of what it's beginning
to break ground with here feeling a
strong six to a light seven on this one
